# Bell Data Intelligence — git ignore
# ====================================
# Local-only data, secrets, and build artifacts. None of this belongs on GitHub.

# ─── macOS / OS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/

# ─── Node ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
*.tsbuildinfo

# ─── Next.js ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.next/
**/.next/
out/
**/out/

# ─── Env files (secrets) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local env files NEVER go to git. Use Railway env vars in production.
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.production
.env.*.local
!.env.example

# ─── Bell local-only data (huge + sensitive) ───────────────────────────────
# The Data/ folder holds raw scraper output (millions of records). Not for git.
# Leading slashes anchor these to the REPO ROOT so they don't accidentally
# match nested folders with the same name (e.g. Portal/server/config/).
/Data/
**/Data/scans/
**/Data/raw/

# Run logs from local Portal sessions
/Operations/
**/Operations/run_logs/
**/Operations/credits/
**/Operations/enrichment_queue/

# Local config — API keys go in macOS Keychain, NOT here, but ignore just in case.
# IMPORTANT: leading slash anchors to repo root only. WITHOUT it, the pattern
# also matched Portal/server/config/ and silently excluded plans.js (the
# bug we hit on 2026-05-27).
/Config/
**/Config/secrets/
**/Config/local/

# ─── Postgres dumps / backups ──────────────────────────────────────────────
*.dump
*.sql.gz
*.backup

# ─── Misc ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
.cache/

# Local-only command outputs / temp files
*.tmp
*.temp

# Marketing site Mapbox token if accidentally written to file (it should be env)
**/.mapbox-token
